    <front>
      <div type="printedheader">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7755_p1"> <seg type="com">
                        <note type="addendum" xml:id="K_7755_c0">Nachträgliche Notiz unten links auf Seite 2 von Eschers Hand: <bibl>Adresse: | Captain Frederick E. B. Beaumont | Chairman of the Machine Tunnelling Company of <placeName type="place" key="London (UK)">London</placeName>. | (nähere Adresse in <placeName type="place" key="London (UK)">London</placeName> <choice>
                                    <abbr>S.</abbr>
                                    <expan>Siehe</expan>
                                </choice> oben.)</bibl>
            – Nachträgliche Notiz oben in der Mitte auf Seite 1 von dritter Hand mit roter Farbe: <bibl>926 (<choice>
                                    <abbr>m.</abbr>
                                    <expan>mit</expan>
                                </choice> 1 Beilage)</bibl>.</note>
                    </seg> <lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <fw>Hôtel Baur au lac
            <lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>
                        <placeName type="place" key="Zürich (Stadt)">Zurich</placeName>.</fw>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="address">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7755_p2">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>
          <placeName type="place" key="London (UK)">London</placeName> address</p>
        <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7755_p3">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l4"/>2 Westminster Chambers.
        <lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>Victoria Street
        <lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>
                    <placeName type="place" key="London (UK)">London</placeName>.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7755_p4">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l7"/>
          <date when="1871-08-23">August 23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 1871</date>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7755_p5">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>Dear Sir</p>
      </div>
    </front>
    <body>
            <div>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7755_p6">
                <lb xml:id="p1-l9"/>As the Chairman of the machine tunnelling Company of
        <lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>
                <placeName type="place" key="London (UK)">London</placeName>, &amp; also on the part of <choice>
                        <abbr>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> </abbr>
                        <expan>Monsieur (Herr)</expan>
                    </choice> <persName type="person" key="Brogden Alexander">Brogden</persName>, I beg to submit to
        <lb xml:id="p1-l11"/>you the following provisional offer for the construction of the
        <lb xml:id="p1-l12"/>
                <placeName type="place" key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">S<hi rend="sup">t</hi> Gothard</placeName> tunnel referred to as notre projet<note type="transcript">sic!</note> direct at page
        <lb xml:id="p1-l13"/>99 of the rapport technique sur le chemin de fer du <placeName type="place" key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">S<hi rend="sup">t</hi> <lb xml:id="p1-l14"/>Gothard</placeName>. </p>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7755_p7">
                <lb xml:id="p1-l15"/>We will undertake to complete the work <hi rend="underline">in 9 years</hi>, &amp; anticipate
        <lb xml:id="p1-l16"/>being able to do so <hi rend="underline">in 6</hi>, we understand that there will be a 
        <lb xml:id="p1-l17"/>fine for delay, while a corresponding premium will be given
        <lb xml:id="p1-l18"/>for speed.</p>
      <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7755_p8">
                <lb xml:id="p1-l19"/>Not having yet had an opportunity of examining the ground
        <lb xml:id="p1-l20"/>I am unable at this moment to give you an exact price, but
        <lb xml:id="p1-l21"/>I may say that our tender for the excavation of the tunnel, will
        <lb xml:id="p1-l22"/>be very considerably, below the estimate at page 30 of the annexe
        <lb xml:id="p1-l23"/>to the rapport technique above referred to; for the masonry
        <lb xml:id="p1-l24"/>I propose to offer at so much per cube metre<note type="transcript">sic!</note>, leaving the quantity
        <lb xml:id="p1-l25"/>to be put in to the direction of the Engineer.<pb n="2"/>
            </p>
      <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7755_p9">
                <lb xml:id="p2-l1"/>I may mention that my estimate as to time is based on the supposition
        <lb xml:id="p2-l2"/>put forward at pages 58 &amp; 59 that the rock is of such a character
        <lb xml:id="p2-l3"/>that it can be sunk through approximately at the rate of 2 metres
        <lb xml:id="p2-l4"/>per week &amp; driven horizontally at the rate of 4 metres per week.
        <lb xml:id="p2-l5"/>The machinery which we shall employ is the block diamond drill,
        <lb xml:id="p2-l6"/>which from its simple character will enable us to begin operations
        <lb xml:id="p2-l7"/>in 3 months from the date of the final acceptance of our offer;
        <lb xml:id="p2-l8"/>the machines may be seen in operation in <placeName type="place" key="England">England</placeName> <add>where</add> we are exe<lb break="no" xml:id="p2-l9"/>cuting with them several important works.</p>
      <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7755_p10">
                <lb xml:id="p2-l10"/>I beg you will be good enough to communicate with me, so soon
        <lb xml:id="p2-l11"/>as you are prepared to receive a formal offer, when <choice>
                        <abbr>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> </abbr>
                        <expan>Monsieur (Herr)</expan>
                    </choice> <persName type="person" key="Brogden Alexander">Brogden</persName> <lb xml:id="p2-l12"/>&amp; myself will be ready to fulfill all necessary conditions, &amp; in
        <lb xml:id="p2-l13"/>doing so please give us sufficient time to enable a proper
        <lb xml:id="p2-l14"/>study of the ground to be made.</p>
    </div>
        </body>
    <back>
      <div type="closer">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7755_p11">
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l15"/>Thanking you for the civility you have shown me</p>
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_7755_p12">
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l16"/>I remain yours truly</p>
      </div>
      <div type="address">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7755_p13">
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l17"/>Fred Beaumont.</p>
      </div>
